<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="88" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d88">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 600.119/1026</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the French Deputy High Commissioner</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_DBE1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Billy</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-17">
                                        <hi rend="italic">September 17, 1918</hi>.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_DBE1">de Billy</persName></hi>:
                                I acknowledge the receipt of your letter of July 16<note n="1" xml:id="d88fn1">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_988">p.
                                    988</ref>.</note> in which you inform me that the French
                                Government would be pleased to learn the attitude of this Government
                                towards certain commercial treaties entered into between the
                                Imperial German Government and some of the neutral governments and
                                containing stipulations relative to trade after the war.</p>
                            <p>In reply, I beg to advise you that this Government is not at the
                                present time prepared to define its attitude towards the treaties in
                                question.</p>
                            <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>